</i></p><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Safeguarding adults is critical to ensuring the safety and well-being of vulnerable individuals within our communities. As an essential component of care provision, safeguarding training equips professionals with the knowledge and skills necessary to identify, prevent, and respond to instances of abuse, neglect, and exploitation. In this blog, Rose delves into the importance of safeguarding adults training, exploring key definitions, relevant legislation, and best practices to foster a culture of safety and protection.</span>
